<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-19T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-19T13:00:00-05:00" n="262" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296A/28: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sackett</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-19T19:00:00+01:00">November 19, 1931—7
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 19—2:25
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>223. [Paraphrase.] With reference to the Embassy’s No. 221, 19th of
                                November, 2 p.m. The agreement with France has been reached. I have
                                been officially notified of this since filing the reference
                                telegram. Today, the Germans mailed the note to Basel. [End
                                paraphrase.] It will be published Saturday. A copy will be given me
                                tomorrow at noon. Shall I send full translation?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sackett</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>